s in person:</p><ul><li>Bring your current, government-issued photo identification.</li><li>Bring cash, a money order in the exact amount, a personal check, or a credit or debit card in your name for the certificate you need.</li><li>Visit the The Office of Vital Records is at <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/5JVQ2UVCayN2">7201 Levander Loop, Building C, Austin, TX, 78702</a> between 8 am and 4:30 p.m. Monday through Friday.<ul><li>The last application is accepted until 4:15 p.m.</li><li>Note that our office is usually busiest between 11:00 a.m. – 2:00 p.m. Customers should expect longer wait times during those hours.</li></ul></li><li>For faster service, download and print an application in <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInENGLISH.pdf">English</a> or <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInSPANISH.pdf">Spanish</a> and bring it with you.</li></ul>", "step_description_es": null, "step_description_vi": null}, {"pk": 4, "sort_order": 3, "page": null, "step_description": "<p>2-5 business days online:</p><ul><li>Visit <a href="https://www.vitalchek.com/">www.VitalChek.com</a>.</li><li>Follow the prompts on VitalChek to select which kind of certificate(s) you need.</li><li>Verify your identity by answering the questions on VitalChek.<ul><li>If they cannot verify your identity with their standard questions, you will be instructed to upload a copy of your current government-issued identification and proof of shipping address before your application can be processed. This will delay the processing and delivery time.</li></ul></li><li>Use a credit or debit card (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, or Discover) to pay for your certificate(s).<ul><li>Processing and UPS shipping fees will be added.</li></ul></li></ul>", "step_description_ar": null, "step_description_en": "<p>2-5 business days online:</p><ul><li>Visit <a href="https://www.vitalchek.com/">www.VitalChek.com</a>.</li><li>Follow the prompts on VitalChek to select which kind of certificate(s) you need.</li><li>Verify your identity by answering the questions on VitalChek.<ul><li>If they cannot verify your identity with their standard questions, you will be instructed to upload a copy of your current government-issued identification and proof of shipping address before your application can be processed. This will delay the processing and delivery time.</li></ul></li><li>Use a credit or debit card (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, or Discover) to pay for your certificate(s).<ul><li>Processing and UPS shipping fees will be added.</li></ul></li></ul>", "step_description_es": null, "step_description_vi": null}, {"pk": 5, "sort_order": 4, "page": null, "step_description": "<p>2-3 weeks by mail:</p><ul><li>Mail the following items to Office of Vital Records, PO Box 1088, Austin, TX 78767-1088:<ul><li>A completed and notarized <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInENGLISH.pdf">certificate application in English</a> or a <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInSPANISH.pdf&gt;certificate application in Spanish&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;
                A check or money order in the exact amount payable to the Office of Vital Records.
                &lt;ul&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;Personal checks must be signed by the same person who signs the application.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
            &lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;
                A copy of one of your &lt;a href=">acceptable and current forms of government-issued photo identification</a>.<ul><li>If your home address is different than the address on your ID, also include a proof of residence like a utility bill, voter registration card, etc...</li></ul></li><li>A self-addressed envelope with a stamp. You may use an express mail envelope for faster return delivery. If this is not included, you will not receive the certificate.</li></ul></li><li>If you need the certificate quickly through the mail, use an Express form of delivery, such as FedEx, USPS, or UPS, and send your application to: Office of Vital Records, 7201 Levander Loop, Bldg. C, Austin, TX 78702.</li></ul>", "step_description_ar": null, "step_description_en": "<p>2-3 weeks by mail:</p><ul><li>Mail the following items to Office of Vital Records, PO Box 1088, Austin, TX 78767-1088:<ul><li>A completed and notarized <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInENGLISH.pdf">certificate application in English</a> or a <a href="http://austintexas.gov/sites/default/files/files/Health/VitalRecords/2018_OVR_WalkInSPANISH.pdf&gt;certificate application in Spanish&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;
                A check or money order in the exact amount payable to the Office of Vital Records.
                &lt;ul&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;Personal checks must be signed by the same person who signs the application.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
            &lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;
                A copy of one of your &lt;a href=">acceptable and current forms of government-issued photo identification</a>.<ul><li>If your home address is different than the address on your ID, also include a proof of residence like a utility bill, voter registration card, etc...</li></ul></li><li>A self-addressed envelope with a stamp. You may use an express mail envelope for faster return delivery. If this is not included, you will not receive the certificate.</li></ul></li><li>If you need the certificate quickly through the mail, use an Express form of delivery, such as FedEx, USPS, or UPS, and send your application to: Office of Vital Records, 7201 Levander Loop, Bldg. C, Austin, TX 78702.</li></ul>", "step_description_es": null, "step_description_vi": null}], "contacts": [{"pk": 1, "page": null, "contact": 1}]}

