{"pk": 27, "path": "00010001000L", "depth": 3, "numchild": 0, "title": "Office of Police Oversight", "title_ar": null, "title_en": "Office of Police Oversight", "title_es": "Oficina de Fiscalización de la Policía", "title_vi": null, "draft_title": "Office of Police Oversight", "slug": "police-oversight", "slug_ar": null, "slug_en": "police-oversight", "slug_es": null, "slug_vi": null, "content_type": 48, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/home/police-oversight/", "url_path_ar": "/home/police-oversight/", "url_path_en": "/home/police-oversight/", "url_path_es": "/home/police-oversight/", "url_path_vi": "/home/police-oversight/", "owner": 1, "seo_title": "", "seo_title_ar": null, "seo_title_en": null, "seo_title_es": null, "seo_title_vi": null, "show_in_menus": false, "search_description": "", "search_description_ar": "", "search_description_en": "", "search_description_es": "", "search_description_vi": "", "go_live_at": null, "expire_at": null, "expired": false, "locked": false, "first_published_at": "2019-02-20T22:47:37.903Z", "last_published_at": "2019-02-27T08:00:56.343Z", "latest_revision_created_at": "2019-02-27T08:00:56.276Z", "live_revision": 230, "created_at": "2019-02-20T22:45:45.614Z", "updated_at": "2019-02-27T08:02:22.640Z", "what_we_do": "<p>When people have concerns or complaints about potential police misconduct, those concerns need to be heard, investigated, and resolved. At Austin’s Office of Police Oversight (OPO), everything we do is to promote an atmosphere of earned trust between Austinites and the Austin Police Department (APD). We do this by making it easy, accessible, and safe for Austinites to provide information and start the process. For example, we ensure that:</p><ul><li>There are several reporting options available (email, an online form, telephone, etc.).</li><li>The process is not overwhelming or complex.</li><li>People understand that they can choose to remain anonymous.</li><li>There is follow-through and transparency on the investigation’s status and eventual outcome.</li><li>The community understands what we do, how we do it, and how to reach us.</li></ul><p>Our office also:</p><ul><li>Can start its own complaints independent of specific residents making a complaint.</li><li>Makes recommendations to the City Manager and to APD about individual incidents and investigations, as well as broader policy recommendations.</li><li>Is committed to treating all parties — residents, APD, and the Austin Police Association (APA) — as stakeholders involved in an ongoing conversation. We seek to understand and learn from all perspectives.</li></ul>", "what_we_do_ar": "<p></p>", "what_we_do_en": "<p>When people have concerns or complaints about potential police misconduct, those concerns need to be heard, investigated, and resolved. At Austin’s Office of Police Oversight (OPO), everything we do is to promote an atmosphere of earned trust between Austinites and the Austin Police Department (APD). We do this by making it easy, accessible, and safe for Austinites to provide information and start the process. For example, we ensure that:</p><ul><li>There are several reporting options available (email, an online form, telephone, etc.).</li><li>The process is not overwhelming or complex.</li><li>People understand that they can choose to remain anonymous.</li><li>There is follow-through and transparency on the investigation’s status and eventual outcome.</li><li>The community understands what we do, how we do it, and how to reach us.</li></ul><p>Our office also:</p><ul><li>Can start its own complaints independent of specific residents making a complaint.</li><li>Makes recommendations to the City Manager and to APD about individual incidents and investigations, as well as broader policy recommendations.</li><li>Is committed to treating all parties — residents, APD, and the Austin Police Association (APA) — as stakeholders involved in an ongoing conversation. We seek to understand and learn from all perspectives.</li></ul>", "what_we_do_es": "<p>Cuando las personas tienen preocupaciones o quejas sobre una posible falta de ética de un policía, esas preocupaciones deben ser escuchadas, investigadas y resueltas.</p><p>Logramos hacer esto haciendo que sea más fácil, accesible y seguro para los residentes de Austin proveer información y comenzar el proceso. Logramos hacer esto haciendo que sea más fácil, accesible y seguro para los residentes de Austin proveer información sobre sus interacciones con el Departamento de Policía de Austin. Por ejemplo, nos aseguramos de que:</p><ul><li>Haya varias opciones de reportes disponibles (correo electrónico, formulario en línea, teléfono, etc.).</li><li>El proceso no sea abrumador ni complejo.</li><li>Las personas entiendan que pueden decidir permanecer anónimas.</li><li>El proceso se lleve a una conclusión y haya transparencia sobre el estado y posible resultado de la investigación.</li><li>La comunidad comprenda lo que hacemos, cómo lo hacemos y cómo se pueden comunicar con nosotros.</li></ul><p>Nuestra oficina también:</p><ul><li>Puede comenzar sus propias quejas aunque algún residente específico no presente una queja.</li><li>Presenta recomendaciones al Administrador Municipal y a APD sobre incidentes e investigaciones individuales, así como recomendaciones para políticas más amplias.</li><li>Está comprometida a tratar todas las partes, residentes, APD y la Asociación de Policías de Austin (APA), como partes interesadas en una conversación continua. Una de nuestras metas es comprender y aprender de todas las perspectivas.</li></ul>", "what_we_do_vi": "<p></p>", "image": 19, "mission": "The mission of the Office of Police Oversight (OPO) is to provide impartial oversight of the Austin Police Department’s conduct, practices, and policies to enhance accountability, inform the public to increase transparency, and create sustainable partnerships throughout the community.", "mission_ar": "", "mission_en": "The mission of the Office of Police Oversight (OPO) is to provide impartial oversight of the Austin Police Department’s conduct, practices, and policies to enhance accountability, inform the public to increase transparency, and create sustainable partnerships throughout the community.", "mission_es": "La misión de la Oficina de Fiscalización de la Policía (OPO) es supervisar de manera imparcial la conducta, prácticas y políticas del Departamento de Policía de Austin para mejorar la responsabilidad y transparencia y establecer confianza entre la comunidad de Austin y los funcionarios de policía.", "mission_vi": "", "social_media": "[]", "job_listings": "", "department_directors": [{"pk": 1, "sort_order": 0, "page": 27, "name": "Farah C. Muscadin", "photo": 20, "about": "Farah was appointed to her role due to her wide range of experience and expertise, and for her demonstrated commitment to fairness and transparency. Farah’s mission is to improve trust between Austin residents and the Austin Police Department.

Farah studied business and law and holds a Juris Doctorate from the University of Iowa College of Law. She served in leadership roles at Chicago State University, Cook County Public Defender’s office, and for the Mayor of the City of Chicago. Her community involvement includes being a mentor through the GirlForward organization and serving on the board of YWCA Greater Austin.", "about_ar": "", "about_en": "Farah was appointed to her role due to her wide range of experience and expertise, and for her demonstrated commitment to fairness and transparency. Farah’s mission is to improve trust between Austin residents and the Austin Police Department.

Farah studied business and law and holds a Juris Doctorate from the University of Iowa College of Law. She served in leadership roles at Chicago State University, Cook County Public Defender’s office, and for the Mayor of the City of Chicago. Her community involvement includes being a mentor through the GirlForward organization and serving on the board of YWCA Greater Austin.", "about_es": "Farah fue designada en su función gracias a su amplia experiencia y por haber demostrado un gran compromiso con la justicia y transparencia. La misión de Farah es mejorar la confianza entre los residentes de Austin y el Departamento de Policía de Austin. Farah estudió administración de empresas y leyes y tiene un doctorado en jurisprudencia de la Escuela de Derecho de la Universidad de Iowa. Ejerció funciones de liderazgo en la Universidad Estatal de Chicago, la oficina del Defensor Público del Condado Cook y para el Alcalde de la Ciudad de Chicago. Su trabajo comunitario incluye ser mentora a través de la organización GirlForward y participar en la junta directiva de YMCA Greater Austin.", "about_vi": "", "email": "policeoversight@austintexas.gov", "phone": "(512) 974-9090"}], "contacts": [{"pk": 1, "page": 27, "contact": 2}]}

